 產品還未上市就因為擔心未來效能不足而砍掉重練 (還換了個程式語言), 聽起來是個 anti-pattern.


Jimmy Chen:
March 27th, 2011 at 7:55 am
 yeah... you should never pre-planned too much. It is indeed "anti-pattern"! I still have nightmare about it. It just isn't lean... but in the end, the reason we end up switching the database is that we just don't feel mysql is the most efficient database for messaging and that phpfox's framework is just too rigid for feature development... hence, we made a really tough decision to make a change now before it's too late...


Ryan Carag:
March 27th, 2011 at 11:56 am
 There is always tension between shipping something fast and shipping something great. Either way, the fundamental goal is still the same: Delight users, whether you have one (lean) feature or 100 features and whether there are a handful of users or millions. The decision really is about placing our bets on what we think gives us the best shot at achieving this fundamental goal in scale.


